snippet.textDisplay: I don't get what the big deal is about MacBooks. From my experience, there are many windows computers that offer far more value and power than the MacBooks. Plus, I see those things all the time go in for repairs. I guess if you want to live within their ecosystem, go for it but running through their OS, I haven't seen any day to day usage that made it better than say, my Lenovo C930. Keep in my mind, the C930 was the current model and I got it on sale for just about $50 more than the MacBooks Airs. To me, that just makes me embarrassed for Apple.

I would say that buying the laptop wouldn't be worth it due to the risk factors. I have noticed the speakers of the 2020 version of Apples' Mac book Pro has a higher quality than the Mac book Air.
